70 bool VendorItemData::RemoveItem(uint32 item_id)
71 {
72  bool found = false;
73  for (VendorItemList::iterator i = m_items.begin(); i != m_items.end();)
74  {
75  // can have many examples
76  if ((*i)->item == item_id)
77  {
78  i = m_items.erase(i);
79  found = true;
80  }
81  else
82  ++i;
83  }
84 
85  return found;

108 void CreatureCreatePos::SelectFinalPoint(Creature* cr, bool staticSpawn)
109 {
110  // if object provided then selected point at specific dist/angle from object forward look
111  if (m_closeObject)
112  {
113  if (m_dist == 0.0f)
114  {
115  m_pos.x = m_closeObject->GetPositionX();
116  m_pos.y = m_closeObject->GetPositionY();
117  m_pos.z = m_closeObject->GetPositionZ();
118  }
119  else
120  m_closeObject->GetClosePoint(m_pos.x, m_pos.y, m_pos.z, cr->GetObjectBoundingRadius(), m_dist, m_angle);
121  }
122  else if (!staticSpawn)
123  cr->UpdateAllowedPositionZ(m_pos.x, m_pos.y, m_pos.z);

165 void Creature::AddToWorld()
166 {
168  if (!IsInWorld())
169  {
170  if (GetObjectGuid().IsCreatureOrVehicle())
171  GetMap()->GetObjectsStore().insert<Creature>(GetObjectGuid(), (Creature*)this);
172  if (GetDbGuid())
173  GetMap()->AddDbGuidObject(this);
174  }
175 
176  switch (GetSubtype())
177  {
178  case CREATURE_SUBTYPE_PET:
179  case CREATURE_SUBTYPE_TEMPORARY_SUMMON:
180  {
181  std::map<uint32, uint32>& targetArray = GetMap()->GetTempCreatures();
182  if (GetSubtype() == CREATURE_SUBTYPE_PET)
183  targetArray = GetMap()->GetTempPets();
184  // If creature exists, add count
185  if (targetArray.find(this->GetEntry()) != targetArray.end())
186  ++targetArray[this->GetEntry()];
187  else
188  targetArray.insert(std::pair<uint32, uint32>(this->GetEntry(), 1));
189  break;
190  }
191  default: break;
192  }
193 
194  Unit::AddToWorld();
195 
196  // Make active if required
197  if (sWorld.isForceLoadMap(GetMapId()) || (GetCreatureInfo()->ExtraFlags & CREATURE_EXTRA_FLAG_ACTIVE))
198  SetActiveObjectState(true);
199 
200  if (m_countSpawns)
201  GetMap()->AddToSpawnCount(GetObjectGuid());
202 }
203 
204 void Creature::RemoveFromWorld()
205 {
207  if (IsInWorld())
208  {
209  if (GetObjectGuid().IsCreatureOrVehicle())
210  GetMap()->GetObjectsStore().erase<Creature>(GetObjectGuid(), (Creature*)nullptr);
211  if (GetDbGuid())
212  GetMap()->RemoveDbGuidObject(this);
213 
214  switch (GetSubtype())
215  {
216  case CREATURE_SUBTYPE_PET:
217  case CREATURE_SUBTYPE_TEMPORARY_SUMMON:
218  {
219  std::map<uint32, uint32>& targetArray = GetMap()->GetTempCreatures();
220  if (GetSubtype() == CREATURE_SUBTYPE_PET)
221  targetArray = GetMap()->GetTempPets();
222  if (targetArray.find(this->GetEntry()) != targetArray.end())
223  {
224  --targetArray[this->GetEntry()];
225 
226  if (targetArray[this->GetEntry()] <= 0)
227  targetArray.erase(this->GetEntry());
228  }
229  break;
230  }
231  default: break;
232  }
233 
234  if (m_countSpawns)
235  GetMap()->RemoveFromSpawnCount(GetObjectGuid());
236 
237  if (uint32 spellId = GetCreatedBySpellId())
238  if (Unit* spawner = GetSpawner())
239  spawner->RemoveCreature(spellId, false);
240 
241  if (GetUInt32Value(UNIT_CREATED_BY_SPELL)) // optimization
242  if (Unit* owner = GetOwner())
243  StartCooldown(owner);
244 
245  ClearCreatureGroup();
246 
247  if (AI())
248  AI()->RelinquishFollow(ObjectGuid());
249  }
250 
251  Unit::RemoveFromWorld();
252 }

263 void Creature::RemoveCorpse(bool inPlace)
264 {
265  if (!inPlace && !IsInWorld())
266  return;
267 
268  if ((GetDeathState() != CORPSE))
269  return;
270 
271  DEBUG_FILTER_LOG(LOG_FILTER_AI_AND_MOVEGENSS, "Removing corpse of %s ", GetGuidStr().c_str());
272 
273  m_corpseExpirationTime = TimePoint();
274  SetDeathState(DEAD);
275  UpdateObjectVisibility();
276 
277  delete m_loot;
278  m_loot = nullptr;
279  m_lootStatus = CREATURE_LOOT_STATUS_NONE;
280  uint32 respawnDelay = 0;
281 
282  if (AI())
283  AI()->CorpseRemoved(respawnDelay);
284 
285  if (m_isCreatureLinkingTrigger)
286  GetMap()->GetCreatureLinkingHolder()->DoCreatureLinkingEvent(LINKING_EVENT_DESPAWN, this);
287 
288  if (InstanceData* mapInstance = GetInstanceData())
289  mapInstance->OnCreatureDespawn(this);
290 
291  // script can set time (in seconds) explicit, override the original
292  if (respawnDelay)
293  {
294  m_respawnTime = time(nullptr) + respawnDelay; // if we set a custom respawn time, we need to save it as well
295 
296  // always save boss respawn time at death to prevent crash cheating
297  if (sWorld.getConfig(CONFIG_BOOL_SAVE_RESPAWN_TIME_IMMEDIATELY) || IsWorldBoss())
298  SaveRespawnTime();
299  }
300 
301  InterruptMoving();
302 
303  float x, y, z, o;
304  GetRespawnCoord(x, y, z, &o);
305  GetMap()->CreatureRelocation(this, x, y, z, o);
306 
307  // forced recreate creature object at clients
308  UnitVisibility currentVis = GetVisibility();
309  SetVisibility(VISIBILITY_REMOVE_CORPSE);
310  UpdateObjectVisibility();
311  SetVisibility(currentVis); // restore visibility state
312  UpdateObjectVisibility();
313 
314  if (IsUsingNewSpawningSystem())
315  AddObjectToRemoveList();
316 }

321 bool Creature::InitEntry(uint32 Entry, CreatureData const* data /*=nullptr*/, GameEventCreatureData const* eventData /*=nullptr*/)
322 {
323  // use game event entry if any instead default suggested
324  if (eventData && eventData->entry_id)
325  Entry = eventData->entry_id;
326 
327  CreatureInfo const* normalInfo = ObjectMgr::GetCreatureTemplate(Entry);
328  if (!normalInfo)
329  {
330  sLog.outErrorDb("Creature::UpdateEntry creature entry %u does not exist.", Entry);
331  return false;
332  }
333 
334  CreatureInfo const* cinfo = normalInfo;
335  for (Difficulty diff = GetMap()->GetDifficulty(); diff > REGULAR_DIFFICULTY; diff = GetPrevDifficulty(diff, GetMap()->IsRaid()))
336  {
337  // we already have valid Map pointer for current creature!
338  if (normalInfo->DifficultyEntry[diff - 1])
339  {
340  cinfo = ObjectMgr::GetCreatureTemplate(normalInfo->DifficultyEntry[diff - 1]);
341  if (cinfo)
342  break; // template found
343 
344  // check and reported at startup, so just ignore (restore normalInfo)
345  cinfo = normalInfo;
346  }
347  }
348 
349  SetEntry(Entry); // normal entry always
350  m_creatureInfo = cinfo; // map mode related always
351 
352  SetObjectScale(cinfo->Scale);
353 
354  SetFloatValue(UNIT_FIELD_HOVERHEIGHT, cinfo->HoverHeight);
355 
356  // equal to player Race field, but creature does not have race
357  SetByteValue(UNIT_FIELD_BYTES_0, UNIT_BYTES_0_OFFSET_RACE, 0);
358 
359  // known valid are: CLASS_WARRIOR,CLASS_PALADIN,CLASS_ROGUE,CLASS_MAGE
360  SetByteValue(UNIT_FIELD_BYTES_0, UNIT_BYTES_0_OFFSET_CLASS, uint8(cinfo->UnitClass));
361 
362  uint32 display_id = ChooseDisplayId(GetCreatureInfo(), data, eventData);
363  if (!display_id) // Cancel load if no display id
364  {
365  sLog.outErrorDb("Creature (Entry: %u) has no model defined in table `creature_template`, can't load.", Entry);
366  return false;
367  }
368 
369  CreatureModelInfo const* minfo = sObjectMgr.GetCreatureModelRandomGender(display_id);
370  if (!minfo) // Cancel load if no model defined
371  {
372  sLog.outErrorDb("Creature (Entry: %u) has no model info defined in table `creature_model_info`, can't load.", Entry);
373  return false;
374  }
375 
376  display_id = minfo->modelid; // it can be different (for another gender)
377 
378  SetNativeDisplayId(display_id);
379 
380  // normally the same as native, but some has exceptions (Spell::DoSummonTotem)
381  // also recalculates speed since speed is based on Model and/or template
382  SetDisplayId(display_id);
383 
384  SetByteValue(UNIT_FIELD_BYTES_0, UNIT_BYTES_0_OFFSET_GENDER, minfo->gender);
385 
386  // set PowerType based on unit class
387  switch (cinfo->UnitClass)
388  {
389  case CLASS_WARRIOR:
390  SetPowerType(POWER_RAGE);
391  break;
392  case CLASS_PALADIN:
393  case CLASS_MAGE:
394  SetPowerType(POWER_MANA);
395  break;
396  case CLASS_ROGUE:
397  SetPowerType(POWER_ENERGY);
398  break;
399  default:
400  sLog.outErrorDb("Creature (Entry: %u) has unhandled unit class. Power type will not be set!", Entry);
401  break;
402  }
403 
404  // Load creature equipment
405  if (eventData)
406  {
407  if (eventData->equipment_id)
408  LoadEquipment(eventData->equipment_id); // use event equipment if any for active event
409  else if (eventData->entry_id)
410  LoadEquipment(cinfo->EquipmentTemplateId, true); // use changed entry default template
411  }
412  else if (!data || (data->spawnTemplate->equipmentId == -1))
413  {
414  if (cinfo->EquipmentTemplateId == 0)
415  LoadEquipment(normalInfo->EquipmentTemplateId, true); // use default from normal template if diff does not have any
416  else
417  LoadEquipment(cinfo->EquipmentTemplateId); // else use from diff template
418  }
419  else if (data)
420  {
421  // override, 0 means no equipment
422  if (data->spawnTemplate->equipmentId != -1)
423  {
424  if (data->spawnTemplate->equipmentId != 0)
425  LoadEquipment(data->spawnTemplate->equipmentId);
426  }
427  }
428 
429  SetName(normalInfo->Name); // at normal entry always
430 
431  SetFloatValue(UNIT_MOD_CAST_SPEED, 1.0f);
432 
433  if (!IsPet() || !static_cast<Pet*>(this)->isControlled())
434  SetLevitate((cinfo->InhabitType & INHABIT_AIR) != 0); // TODO: may not be correct to send opcode at this point (already handled by UPDATE_OBJECT createObject)
435 
436  // check if we need to add swimming movement. TODO: i thing movement flags should be computed automatically at each movement of creature so we need a sort of UpdateMovementFlags() method
437  if (cinfo->InhabitType & INHABIT_WATER && // check inhabit type water
438  !(cinfo->ExtraFlags & CREATURE_EXTRA_FLAG_WALK_IN_WATER) && // check if creature is forced to walk (crabs, giant,...)
439  GetMap()->GetTerrain()->IsSwimmable(m_respawnPos.x, m_respawnPos.y, m_respawnPos.z, GetCollisionHeight())) // check if creature is in water and have enough space to swim
440  m_movementInfo.AddMovementFlag(MOVEFLAG_SWIMMING); // add swimming movement
441 
442  // checked at loading
443  if (data)
444  {
445  if (data->spawnTemplate->IsRunning())
446  SetWalk(false);
447  if (data->spawnTemplate->IsHovering())
448  SetHover(true);
449  m_defaultMovementType = MovementGeneratorType(data->movementType);
450  }
451  else
452  m_defaultMovementType = MovementGeneratorType(cinfo->MovementType);
453 
454  SetMeleeDamageSchool(SpellSchools(cinfo->DamageSchool));
455 
456  SetCanParry(!(cinfo->ExtraFlags & CREATURE_EXTRA_FLAG_NO_PARRY));
457  SetCanBlock(!(cinfo->ExtraFlags & CREATURE_EXTRA_FLAG_NO_BLOCK));
458  SetCanDualWield((cinfo->ExtraFlags & CREATURE_EXTRA_FLAG_DUAL_WIELD_FORCED));
459  SetForceAttackingCapability((cinfo->ExtraFlags & CREATURE_EXTRA_FLAG_FORCE_ATTACKING_CAPABILITY) != 0);
460  SetCanCallForAssistance((cinfo->ExtraFlags & CREATURE_EXTRA_FLAG_NO_CALL_ASSIST) == 0);
461  SetNoReputation(false);
462 
463  SetDetectionRange(cinfo->Detection);
464 
465  if (cinfo->CorpseDelay)
466  SetCorpseDelay(cinfo->CorpseDelay);
467  else if(sObjectMgr.IsEncounter(GetEntry(), GetMapId()))
468  {
469  // encounter boss forced decay timer to 1h
470  m_corpseDelay = 3600; // TODO: maybe add that to config file
471  }
472  else
473  {
474  switch (cinfo->Rank)
475  {
476  case CREATURE_ELITE_RARE:
477  m_corpseDelay = sWorld.getConfig(CONFIG_UINT32_CORPSE_DECAY_RARE);
478  break;
479  case CREATURE_ELITE_ELITE:
480  m_corpseDelay = sWorld.getConfig(CONFIG_UINT32_CORPSE_DECAY_ELITE);
481  break;
482  case CREATURE_ELITE_RAREELITE:
483  m_corpseDelay = sWorld.getConfig(CONFIG_UINT32_CORPSE_DECAY_RAREELITE);
484  break;
485  case CREATURE_ELITE_WORLDBOSS:
486  m_corpseDelay = sWorld.getConfig(CONFIG_UINT32_CORPSE_DECAY_WORLDBOSS);
487  break;
488  default:
489  m_corpseDelay = sWorld.getConfig(CONFIG_UINT32_CORPSE_DECAY_NORMAL);
490  break;
491  }
492  }
493 
494  if (cinfo->InteractionPauseTimer != -1)
495  m_interactionPauseTimer = cinfo->InteractionPauseTimer;
496  else
497  m_interactionPauseTimer = sWorld.getConfig(CONFIG_UINT32_INTERACTION_PAUSE_TIMER);
498 
499  return true;
500 }

502 bool Creature::UpdateEntry(uint32 Entry, const CreatureData* data /*=nullptr*/, GameEventCreatureData const* eventData /*=nullptr*/, bool preserveHPAndPower /*=true*/, bool randomizeLevels/*= true*/)
503 {
504  if (!InitEntry(Entry, data, eventData))
505  return false;
506 
507  // creatures always have melee weapon ready if any
508  SetSheath(SHEATH_STATE_MELEE);
509 
510  if (preserveHPAndPower)
511  {
512  uint32 healthPercent = GetHealthPercent();
513  SelectLevel(randomizeLevels ? USE_DEFAULT_DATABASE_LEVEL : GetLevel());
514  SetHealthPercent(healthPercent);
515  }
516  else
517  {
518  SelectLevel(randomizeLevels ? USE_DEFAULT_DATABASE_LEVEL : GetLevel());
519  if (data)
520  {
521  uint32 curhealth = data->spawnTemplate->curHealth > 0 ? data->spawnTemplate->curHealth : GetMaxHealth();
522  SetHealth(m_deathState == ALIVE ? curhealth : 0);
523  if (GetPowerType() == POWER_MANA)
524  {
525  uint32 curmana;
526  uint32 newPossibleData = data->spawnTemplate->curMana;
527  if (IsRegeneratingPower()) // bypass so that 0 mana is possible TODO: change this to -1 in DB
528  curmana = newPossibleData ? newPossibleData : GetMaxPower(POWER_MANA);
529  else
530  curmana = newPossibleData;
531  SetPower(POWER_MANA, curmana);
532  }
533  }
534  }
535 
536  uint32 faction = GetCreatureInfo()->Faction;
537  if (data && data->spawnTemplate->faction)
538  faction = data->spawnTemplate->faction;
539  setFaction(faction);
540 
541  SetDefaultGossipMenuId(GetCreatureInfo()->GossipMenuId);
542 
543  uint32 npcFlags = GetCreatureInfo()->NpcFlags;
544  if (data && data->spawnTemplate->npcFlags != -1)
545  npcFlags = uint32(data->spawnTemplate->npcFlags);
546  SetUInt32Value(UNIT_NPC_FLAGS, npcFlags);
547 
548  uint32 attackTimer = GetCreatureInfo()->MeleeBaseAttackTime;
549 
550  SetAttackTime(BASE_ATTACK, attackTimer);
551  SetAttackTime(OFF_ATTACK, attackTimer);
552  SetAttackTime(RANGED_ATTACK, GetCreatureInfo()->RangedBaseAttackTime);
553 
554  uint32 unitFlags = GetCreatureInfo()->UnitFlags;
555  if (data && data->spawnTemplate->unitFlags != -1)
556  unitFlags = uint32(data->spawnTemplate->unitFlags);
557 
558  // we may need to append or remove additional flags
559  if (HasFlag(UNIT_FIELD_FLAGS, UNIT_FLAG_IN_COMBAT))
560  unitFlags |= UNIT_FLAG_IN_COMBAT;
561 
562  // TODO: Get rid of this by fixing DB data, seems to be static
563  if (m_movementInfo.HasMovementFlag(MOVEFLAG_SWIMMING))
564  unitFlags |= UNIT_FLAG_SWIMMING;
565 
566  SetUInt32Value(UNIT_FIELD_FLAGS, unitFlags);
567  SetUInt32Value(UNIT_FIELD_FLAGS_2, GetCreatureInfo()->UnitFlags2);
568 
569  // preserve all current dynamic flags if exist
570  uint32 dynFlags = GetUInt32Value(UNIT_DYNAMIC_FLAGS);
571  SetUInt32Value(UNIT_DYNAMIC_FLAGS, dynFlags ? dynFlags : GetCreatureInfo()->DynamicFlags);
572 
573  SetCreateResistance(SPELL_SCHOOL_HOLY, GetCreatureInfo()->ResistanceHoly);
574  SetCreateResistance(SPELL_SCHOOL_FIRE, GetCreatureInfo()->ResistanceFire);
575  SetCreateResistance(SPELL_SCHOOL_NATURE, GetCreatureInfo()->ResistanceNature);
576  SetCreateResistance(SPELL_SCHOOL_FROST, GetCreatureInfo()->ResistanceFrost);
577  SetCreateResistance(SPELL_SCHOOL_SHADOW, GetCreatureInfo()->ResistanceShadow);
578  SetCreateResistance(SPELL_SCHOOL_ARCANE, GetCreatureInfo()->ResistanceArcane);
579 
580  m_isInvisible = (GetCreatureInfo()->ExtraFlags & CREATURE_EXTRA_FLAG_INVISIBLE) != 0;
581  m_ignoreMMAP = (GetCreatureInfo()->ExtraFlags & CREATURE_EXTRA_FLAG_MMAP_FORCE_DISABLE) != 0;
582  m_countSpawns = (GetCreatureInfo()->ExtraFlags & CREATURE_EXTRA_FLAG_COUNT_SPAWNS) != 0;
583  if (IsWorldBoss())
584  ApplySpellImmune(nullptr, IMMUNITY_STATE, SPELL_AURA_MOD_TOTAL_STAT_PERCENTAGE, true);
585 
586  if ((GetCreatureInfo()->RegenerateStats & (REGEN_FLAG_POWER_IN_COMBAT | REGEN_FLAG_POWER)) == (REGEN_FLAG_POWER_IN_COMBAT | REGEN_FLAG_POWER))
587  SetFlag(UNIT_FIELD_FLAGS_2, UNIT_FLAG2_REGENERATE_POWER);
588 
589  SetCanModifyStats(true);
590  UpdateAllStats();
591 
592  // checked and error show at loading templates
593  if (FactionTemplateEntry const* factionTemplate = sFactionTemplateStore.LookupEntry(faction))
594  {
595  if (factionTemplate->factionFlags & FACTION_TEMPLATE_FLAG_ASSIST_PLAYERS)
596  {
597  const AreaTableEntry* zone = GetAreaEntryByAreaID(GetAreaId());
598  const bool sanctuary = (zone && (zone->flags & AREA_FLAG_SANCTUARY));
599  SetPvP(!sanctuary);
600  }

619 
620  if (GetCreatureInfo()->StringID1)
621  SetStringId(GetCreatureInfo()->StringID1, true);
622 
623  if (GetCreatureInfo()->StringID2)
624  SetStringId(GetCreatureInfo()->StringID2, true);
625 
626  if (data && data->spawnTemplate->stringId)
627  SetStringId(data->spawnTemplate->stringId, true);
628 
629  // static flags implementation

659 uint32 Creature::ChooseDisplayId(const CreatureInfo* cinfo, const CreatureData* data /*= nullptr*/, GameEventCreatureData const* eventData /*=nullptr*/)
660 {
661  // Use creature event model explicit, override any other static models
662  if (eventData && eventData->modelid)
663  return eventData->modelid;
664 
665  // Use creature model explicit, override template (creature.modelid)
666  if (data)
667  {
668  if (data->spawnTemplate->modelId)
669  return data->spawnTemplate->modelId;
670  }
671 
672  // use defaults from the template
673  uint32 display_id = 0;
674 
675  // models may be categorized as (in this order):
676  // if mod4 && mod3 && mod2 && mod1 use any, by 25%-chance (other gender is selected and replaced after this function)
677  // if mod3 && mod2 && mod1 use mod3 unless mod2 has modelid_alt_model (then all by 33%-chance)
678  // if mod2 use mod2 unless mod2 has modelid_alt_model (then both by 50%-chance)
679  // if mod1 use mod1
680 
681  // The follow decision tree needs to be updated if MAX_CREATURE_MODEL is changed.
682  static_assert(MAX_CREATURE_MODEL == 4, "Need to update model selection code for new or removed model fields");
683 
684  // model selected here may be replaced with other_gender using own function
685  if (cinfo->ModelId[3] && cinfo->ModelId[2] && cinfo->ModelId[1] && cinfo->ModelId[0])
686  {
687  display_id = cinfo->ModelId[urand(0, 3)];
688  }
689  else if (cinfo->ModelId[2] && cinfo->ModelId[1] && cinfo->ModelId[0])
690  {
691  uint32 modelid_tmp = sObjectMgr.GetCreatureModelAlternativeModel(cinfo->ModelId[1]);
692  display_id = modelid_tmp ? cinfo->ModelId[urand(0, 2)] : cinfo->ModelId[2];
693  }
694  else if (cinfo->ModelId[1])
695  {
696  // We use this to eliminate invisible models vs. "dummy" models (infernals, etc).
697  // Where it's expected to select one of two, model must have a alternative model defined (alternative model is normally the same as defined in ModelId1).
698  // Same pattern is used in the above model selection, but the result may be ModelId3 and not ModelId2 as here.
699  uint32 modelid_tmp = sObjectMgr.GetCreatureModelAlternativeModel(cinfo->ModelId[1]);
700  display_id = modelid_tmp ? cinfo->ModelId[urand(0, 1)] : cinfo->ModelId[1];
701  }
702  else if (cinfo->ModelId[0])
703  {
704  display_id = cinfo->ModelId[0];
705  }
706 
707  // fail safe, we use creature entry 1 and make error
708  if (!display_id)
709  {
710  sLog.outErrorDb("Call customer support, ChooseDisplayId can not select native model for creature entry %u, model from creature entry 1 will be used instead.", cinfo->Entry);
711 
712  if (const CreatureInfo* creatureDefault = ObjectMgr::GetCreatureTemplate(1))
713  display_id = creatureDefault->ModelId[0];
714  }
715 
716  return display_id;
717 }

719 void Creature::Update(const uint32 diff)
720 {
721  switch (m_deathState)
722  {
723  case JUST_ALIVED:
724  // Don't must be called, see Creature::SetDeathState JUST_ALIVED -> ALIVE promoting.
725  sLog.outError("Creature (GUIDLow: %u Entry: %u ) in wrong state: JUST_ALIVED (4)", GetGUIDLow(), GetEntry());
726  break;
727  case JUST_DIED:
728  // Don't must be called, see Creature::SetDeathState JUST_DIED -> CORPSE promoting.
729  sLog.outError("Creature (GUIDLow: %u Entry: %u ) in wrong state: JUST_DEAD (1)", GetGUIDLow(), GetEntry());
730  break;
731  case DEAD:
732  {
733  if (m_respawnTime <= time(nullptr) && (!m_isSpawningLinked || GetMap()->GetCreatureLinkingHolder()->CanSpawn(this)))
734  {
735  DEBUG_FILTER_LOG(LOG_FILTER_AI_AND_MOVEGENSS, "Respawning...");
736  m_respawnTime = 0;
737  SetCanAggro(false);
738  delete m_loot;
739  m_loot = nullptr;
740 
741  // Clear possible auras having IsDeathPersistent() attribute
742  RemoveAllAuras();
743 
744  SetUInt32Value(UNIT_DYNAMIC_FLAGS, UNIT_DYNFLAG_NONE);
745  SetDeathState(JUST_ALIVED);
746 
747  // Call AI respawn virtual function
748  if (AI())
749  AI()->JustRespawned();
750 
751  // Inform Instance Data
752  if (InstanceData* mapInstance = GetInstanceData())
753  mapInstance->OnCreatureRespawn(this);
754 
755  if (m_isCreatureLinkingTrigger)
756  GetMap()->GetCreatureLinkingHolder()->DoCreatureLinkingEvent(LINKING_EVENT_RESPAWN, this);
757 
758  if (GetCreatureGroup())
759  GetCreatureGroup()->TriggerLinkingEvent(CREATURE_GROUP_EVENT_RESPAWN, this);
760 
761  GetMap()->Add(this);
762 
763  if (GetObjectGuid().GetHigh() != HIGHGUID_PET)
764  if (uint16 poolid = sPoolMgr.IsPartOfAPool<Creature>(GetDbGuid()))
765  sPoolMgr.UpdatePool<Creature>(*GetMap()->GetPersistentState(), poolid, GetDbGuid());
766  }
767  break;
768  }
769  case CORPSE:
770  {
771  Unit::Update(diff);
772 
773  if (m_loot)
774  m_loot->Update();
775 
776  if (IsCorpseExpired())
777  RemoveCorpse();
778 
779  break;
780  }
781  case ALIVE:
782  {
783  Unit::Update(diff);
784 
785  // creature can be dead after Unit::Update call
786  // CORPSE/DEAD state will processed at next tick (in other case death timer will be updated unexpectedly)
787  if (!IsAlive())
788  break;
789 
790  // Creature can be dead after unit update
791  if (IsAlive())
792  RegenerateAll(diff);
793 
794  break;
795  }
796  default:
797  break;
798  }
799 }

801 void Creature::RegenerateAll(uint32 diff)
802 {
803  m_regenTimer += diff;
804  if (m_regenTimer < REGEN_TIME_FULL_UNIT)
805  return;
806 
807  if (!IsInCombat() || GetCombatManager().IsEvadeRegen())
808  RegenerateHealth();
809 
810  RegeneratePower(REGEN_TIME_FULL_UNIT / 1000);
811 
812  m_regenTimer -= REGEN_TIME_FULL_UNIT;
813 }

815 void Creature::RegeneratePower(float timerMultiplier)
816 {
817  if (!IsRegeneratingPower())
818  return;
819 
820  Powers powerType = GetPowerType();
821  uint32 curValue = GetPower(powerType);
822  uint32 maxValue = GetMaxPower(powerType);
823 
824  if (curValue >= maxValue)
825  return;
826 
827  float addValue = 0.0f;
828 
829  switch (powerType)
830  {
831  case POWER_MANA:
832  // Combat and any controlled creature
833  if (IsInCombat() || GetMasterGuid())
834  {
835  if (!IsUnderLastManaUseEffect())
836  {
837  float ManaIncreaseRate = sWorld.getConfig(CONFIG_FLOAT_RATE_POWER_MANA);
838  float intellect = GetStat(STAT_INTELLECT);
839  addValue = sqrt(intellect) * OCTRegenMPPerSpirit() * ManaIncreaseRate / 5.f * timerMultiplier;
840  if (!IsPet() && !HasFlag(UNIT_FIELD_FLAGS, UNIT_FLAG_PLAYER_CONTROLLED) && addValue == 0.f)
841  addValue = (GetMaxPower(POWER_MANA) / 20) / 5.f * timerMultiplier;
842  }
843  }
844  else
845  addValue = maxValue / 3.0f;
846  break;
847  case POWER_ENERGY:
848  addValue = 10 * sWorld.getConfig(CONFIG_FLOAT_RATE_POWER_ENERGY) * timerMultiplier;
849  break;
850  case POWER_FOCUS:
851  addValue = 12 * sWorld.getConfig(CONFIG_FLOAT_RATE_POWER_FOCUS) * timerMultiplier;
852  break;
853  default:
854  return;
855  }
856 
857  // Apply modifiers (if any)
858  AuraList const& ModPowerRegenAuras = GetAurasByType(SPELL_AURA_MOD_POWER_REGEN);
859  for (auto ModPowerRegenAura : ModPowerRegenAuras)
860  {
861  Modifier const* modifier = ModPowerRegenAura->GetModifier();
862  if (modifier->m_miscvalue == int32(powerType))
863  addValue += modifier->m_amount / 5.f * timerMultiplier;
864  }
865 
866  AuraList const& ModPowerRegenPCTAuras = GetAurasByType(SPELL_AURA_MOD_POWER_REGEN_PERCENT);
867  for (auto ModPowerRegenPCTAura : ModPowerRegenPCTAuras)
868  {
869  Modifier const* modifier = ModPowerRegenPCTAura->GetModifier();
870  if (modifier->m_miscvalue == int32(powerType))
871  addValue *= (modifier->m_amount + 100) / 100.0f;
872  }
873 
874  ModifyPower(powerType, int32(addValue));
875 }

877 void Creature::RegenerateHealth()
878 {
879  if (!IsRegeneratingHealth())
880  return;
881 
882  uint32 curValue = GetHealth();
883  uint32 maxValue = GetMaxHealth();
884 
885  if (curValue >= maxValue)
886  return;
887 
888  // regenerate 33% for npc and ~13% for player controlled npc (enslave etc) ToDo: Find Regenvalue based on Spirit, might differ due to mob types
889  uint32 addvalue = IsPlayerControlled() ? maxValue * 0.13 : maxValue / 3;
890 
891  ModifyHealth(addvalue);
892 }

1172 void Creature::SetLootRecipient(Unit* unit)
1173 {
1174  // set the player whose group should receive the right
1175  // to loot the creature after it dies
1176  // should be set to nullptr after the loot disappears
1177 
1178  if (!unit)
1179  {
1180  m_lootRecipientGuid.Clear();

1182  ForceValuesUpdateAtIndex(UNIT_DYNAMIC_FLAGS); // needed to be sure tapping status is updated

1187  if (!player) // normal creature, no player involved
1188  return;
1189 
1190  // set player for non group case or if group will disbanded
1191  m_lootRecipientGuid = player->GetObjectGuid();
1192 
1193  // set group for group existing case including if player will leave group at loot time
1194  if (Group* group = player->GetGroup())
1195  m_lootGroupRecipientId = group->GetId();
1196 
1197  ForceValuesUpdateAtIndex(UNIT_DYNAMIC_FLAGS); // needed to be sure tapping status is updated

1214 void Creature::SaveToDB(uint32 mapid, uint8 spawnMask, uint32 phaseMask)

1225  // The following if-else assumes that there are 4 model fields and needs updating if this is changed.
1226  static_assert(MAX_CREATURE_MODEL == 4, "Need to update custom model check for new/removed model fields.");
1227 
1228  if (displayId != cinfo->ModelId[0] && displayId != cinfo->ModelId[1] &&
1229  displayId != cinfo->ModelId[2] && displayId != cinfo->ModelId[3])
1230  {
1231  for (int i = 0; i < MAX_CREATURE_MODEL && displayId; ++i)
1232  if (cinfo->ModelId[i])
1233  if (CreatureModelInfo const* minfo = sObjectMgr.GetCreatureModelInfo(cinfo->ModelId[i]))
1234  if (displayId == minfo->modelid_other_gender)
1235  displayId = 0;
1236  }
1237  else
1238  displayId = 0;
1239  }
1240 
1241  // data->guid = guid don't must be update at save
1242  data.id = GetEntry();
1243  data.mapid = mapid;
1244  data.spawnMask = spawnMask;
1245  data.phaseMask = phaseMask;
1246  data.posX = GetPositionX();
1247  data.posY = GetPositionY();
1248  data.posZ = GetPositionZ();
1249  data.orientation = GetOrientation();
1250  data.spawntimesecsmin = m_respawnDelay;
1251  data.spawntimesecsmax = m_respawnDelay;
1252  // prevent add data integrity problems
1253  data.spawndist = GetDefaultMovementType() == IDLE_MOTION_TYPE ? 0 : m_respawnradius;
1254  // prevent add data integrity problems
1255  data.movementType = !m_respawnradius && GetDefaultMovementType() == RANDOM_MOTION_TYPE
1256  ? IDLE_MOTION_TYPE : GetDefaultMovementType();
1257  data.spawnTemplate = sObjectMgr.GetCreatureSpawnTemplate(0);
1258 
1259  // updated in DB
1260  WorldDatabase.BeginTransaction();
1261 
1262  WorldDatabase.PExecuteLog("DELETE FROM creature WHERE guid=%u", GetGUIDLow());
1263 
1264  std::ostringstream ss;
1265  ss << "INSERT INTO creature VALUES ("
1266  << GetGUIDLow() << ","
1267  << data.id << ","
1268  << data.mapid << ","
1269  << static_cast<uint32>(data.spawnMask) << "," // cast to prevent save as symbol
1270  << static_cast<uint16>(data.phaseMask) << "," // prevent out of range error
1271  << data.posX << ","
1272  << data.posY << ","
1273  << data.posZ << ","
1274  << data.orientation << ","

1277  << static_cast<float>(data.spawndist) << "," // spawn distance (float)
1278  << static_cast<uint32>(data.movementType) << ")"; // default movement generator type, cast to prevent save as symbol

1281

1285 void Creature::SelectLevel(uint32 forcedLevel /*= USE_DEFAULT_DATABASE_LEVEL*/)
1286 {
1287  CreatureInfo const* cinfo = GetCreatureInfo();
1288  if (!cinfo)
1289  return;
1290 
1291  uint32 rank = IsPet() ? 0 : cinfo->Rank; // TODO :: IsPet probably not needed here
1292 
1293  // level
1294  uint32 level = forcedLevel;
1295  uint32 const minlevel = cinfo->MinLevel;
1296  uint32 const maxlevel = cinfo->MaxLevel;
1297 
1298  if (level == USE_DEFAULT_DATABASE_LEVEL)
1299  level = minlevel == maxlevel ? minlevel : urand(minlevel, maxlevel);
1300 
1301  SetLevel(level);
1302 
1304  // Calculate level dependent stats
1306 
1307  uint32 health = static_cast<uint32>(-1);
1308  uint32 mana = static_cast<uint32>(-1);
1309  float armor = -1.f;
1310  float mainMinDmg = 0.f;
1311  float mainMaxDmg = 0.f;
1312  float offMinDmg = 0.f;
1313  float offMaxDmg = 0.f;
1314  float minRangedDmg = 0.f;
1315  float maxRangedDmg = 0.f;
1316  float meleeAttackPwr = 0.f;
1317  float rangedAttackPwr = 0.f;
1318 
1319  float damageMod = _GetDamageMod(rank);
1320  float damageMulti = cinfo->DamageMultiplier * damageMod;
1321  bool usedDamageMulti = false;
1322 
1323  if (CreatureClassLvlStats const* cCLS = sObjectMgr.GetCreatureClassLvlStats(level, cinfo->UnitClass, cinfo->Expansion))
1324  {
1325  // Use Creature Stats to calculate stat values
1326 
1327  // health
1328  if (cinfo->HealthMultiplier >= 0)
1329  health = std::round(cCLS->BaseHealth * cinfo->HealthMultiplier);
1330 
1331  // mana
1332  if (cinfo->PowerMultiplier >= 0)
1333  mana = std::round(cCLS->BaseMana * cinfo->PowerMultiplier);
1334 
1335  // armor
1336  if (cinfo->ArmorMultiplier >= 0)
1337  armor = std::round(cCLS->BaseArmor * cinfo->ArmorMultiplier);
1338 
1339  // damage
1340  if (cinfo->DamageMultiplier >= 0)
1341  {
1342  usedDamageMulti = true;
1343  mainMinDmg = ((cCLS->BaseDamage * cinfo->DamageVariance) + (cCLS->BaseMeleeAttackPower / 14.0f)) * (cinfo->MeleeBaseAttackTime / 1000.0f) * damageMulti;
1344  mainMaxDmg = ((cCLS->BaseDamage * cinfo->DamageVariance * 1.5f) + (cCLS->BaseMeleeAttackPower / 14.0f)) * (cinfo->MeleeBaseAttackTime / 1000.0f) * damageMulti;
1345  offMinDmg = mainMinDmg; // Unitmod handles 50%
1346  offMaxDmg = mainMaxDmg;
1347  minRangedDmg = ((cCLS->BaseDamage * cinfo->DamageVariance) + (cCLS->BaseRangedAttackPower / 14.0f)) * (cinfo->RangedBaseAttackTime / 1000.0f) * damageMulti;
1348  maxRangedDmg = ((cCLS->BaseDamage * cinfo->DamageVariance * 1.5f) + (cCLS->BaseRangedAttackPower / 14.0f)) * (cinfo->RangedBaseAttackTime / 1000.0f) * damageMulti;
1349 
1350  // attack power (not sure about the next line)
1351  meleeAttackPwr = cCLS->BaseMeleeAttackPower;
1352  rangedAttackPwr = cCLS->BaseRangedAttackPower;
1353  }
1354  }
1355 
1356  if (!usedDamageMulti || health == -1 || mana == -1 || armor == -1.f) // some field needs to default to old db fields
1357  {
1358  if (forcedLevel == USE_DEFAULT_DATABASE_LEVEL || (forcedLevel >= minlevel && forcedLevel <= maxlevel))
1359  {
1360  // Use old style to calculate stat values
1361  float rellevel = maxlevel == minlevel ? 0 : (float(level - minlevel)) / (maxlevel - minlevel);
1362 
1363  // health
1364  if (health == -1.f)
1365  {
1366  uint32 minhealth = std::min(cinfo->MaxLevelHealth, cinfo->MinLevelHealth);
1367  uint32 maxhealth = std::max(cinfo->MaxLevelHealth, cinfo->MinLevelHealth);
1368  health = uint32(minhealth + uint32(rellevel * (maxhealth - minhealth)));
1369  }
1370 
1371  // mana
1372  if (mana == -1.f)
1373  {
1374  uint32 minmana = std::min(cinfo->MaxLevelMana, cinfo->MinLevelMana);
1375  uint32 maxmana = std::max(cinfo->MaxLevelMana, cinfo->MinLevelMana);
1376  mana = minmana + uint32(rellevel * (maxmana - minmana));
1377  }
1378 
1379  // armor
1380  if (armor == -1.f)
1381  armor = cinfo->Armor;
1382 
1383  // damage
1384  if (!usedDamageMulti)
1385  {
1386  mainMinDmg = cinfo->MinMeleeDmg * damageMulti;
1387  mainMaxDmg = cinfo->MaxMeleeDmg * damageMulti;
1388  offMinDmg = cinfo->MinMeleeDmg * damageMulti;
1389  offMaxDmg = cinfo->MaxMeleeDmg * damageMulti;
1390  minRangedDmg = cinfo->MinRangedDmg * damageMulti;
1391  maxRangedDmg = cinfo->MaxRangedDmg * damageMulti;
1392 
1393  // attack power
1394  meleeAttackPwr = cinfo->MeleeAttackPower;
1395  rangedAttackPwr = cinfo->RangedAttackPower;
1396  }
1397  }
1398  else
1399  {
1400  sLog.outError("Creature::SelectLevel> Error trying to set level(%u) for creature %s without enough data to do it!", level, GetGuidStr().c_str());
1401  // probably wrong
1402  health = (cinfo->MaxLevelHealth / cinfo->MaxLevel) * level;
1403  mana = (cinfo->MaxLevelMana / cinfo->MaxLevel) * level;
1404  armor = 0;
1405  }
1406  }
1407 
1408  health *= _GetHealthMod(rank); // Apply custom config settting
1409  if (health < 1)
1410  health = 1;
1411 
1413  // Set values
1415 
1416  // health
1417  SetCreateHealth(health);
1418  SetMaxHealth(health);
1419  SetHealth(health);
1420 
1421  // all power types
1422  for (int i = POWER_MANA; i <= POWER_RUNIC_POWER; ++i)
1423  {
1424  uint32 maxValue = 0;
1425 
1426  switch (i)
1427  {
1428  case POWER_MANA: maxValue = mana; break;
1429  case POWER_RAGE: maxValue = 0; break;
1430  case POWER_FOCUS: maxValue = POWER_FOCUS_DEFAULT; break;
1431  case POWER_ENERGY: maxValue = 0; break;
1432  case POWER_HAPPINESS: maxValue = POWER_HAPPINESS_DEFAULT; break;
1433  case POWER_RUNE: maxValue = 0; break;
1434  case POWER_RUNIC_POWER: maxValue = 0; break;
1435  }
1436 
1437  uint32 value = maxValue;
1438 
1439  // For non regenerating powers set 0
1440  if ((i == POWER_ENERGY || i == POWER_MANA) && !IsRegeneratingPower())
1441  value = 0;
1442 
1443  // Mana requires an extra field to be set
1444  SetMaxPower(Powers(i), maxValue);
1445  SetPower(Powers(i), value);
1446 
1447  if (i == POWER_MANA)
1448  SetCreateMana(value);
1449  else // do not set modifier for mana
1450  SetModifierValue(UnitMods(UNIT_MOD_POWER_START + i), BASE_VALUE, float(value));
1451  }
1452 
1453  // Armor
1454  SetModifierValue(UNIT_MOD_ARMOR, BASE_VALUE, armor);
1455 
1456  // damage
1457  SetBaseWeaponDamage(BASE_ATTACK, MINDAMAGE, mainMinDmg);
1458  SetBaseWeaponDamage(BASE_ATTACK, MAXDAMAGE, mainMaxDmg);
1459  SetBaseWeaponDamage(OFF_ATTACK, MINDAMAGE, offMinDmg);
1460  SetBaseWeaponDamage(OFF_ATTACK, MAXDAMAGE, offMaxDmg);
1461  SetBaseWeaponDamage(RANGED_ATTACK, MINDAMAGE, minRangedDmg);
1462  SetBaseWeaponDamage(RANGED_ATTACK, MAXDAMAGE, maxRangedDmg);
1463 
1464  // attack power
1465  SetModifierValue(UNIT_MOD_ATTACK_POWER, BASE_VALUE, meleeAttackPwr * damageMod);
1466  SetModifierValue(UNIT_MOD_ATTACK_POWER_RANGED, BASE_VALUE, rangedAttackPwr * damageMod);
1467 
1468  UpdateAllStats();
1469 }

1593 bool Creature::LoadFromDB(uint32 dbGuid, Map* map, uint32 newGuid, uint32 forcedEntry, GenericTransport* transport)
1594 {
1595  CreatureData const* data = sObjectMgr.GetCreatureData(dbGuid);
1596 
1597  if (!data)
1598  {
1599  sLog.outErrorDb("Creature (GUID: %u) not found in table `creature`, can't load. ", dbGuid);
1600  return false;
1601  }
1602 
1603  // Creature can be loaded already in map if grid has been unloaded while creature walk to another grid
1604  {
1605  Creature* existing = map->GetCreature(dbGuid);
1606  if (existing && existing->IsAlive())
1607  return false;
1608  }
1609 
1610  uint32 entry = forcedEntry ? forcedEntry : data->id;
1611 
1612  // get data for dual spawn instances
1613  if (entry == 0)
1614  entry = GetCreatureConditionalSpawnEntry(dbGuid, map);
1615 
1616  SpawnGroupEntry* groupEntry = map->GetMapDataContainer().GetSpawnGroupByGuid(dbGuid, TYPEID_UNIT); // use dynguid by default \o/
1617  CreatureGroup* group = nullptr;

1620  group = static_cast<CreatureGroup*>(map->GetSpawnManager().GetSpawnGroup(groupEntry->Id));
1621  if (!entry)

1631 
1632  CreatureInfo const* cinfo = ObjectMgr::GetCreatureTemplate(entry);
1633  if (!cinfo)

1636  return false;
1637  }
1638 
1639  bool dynguid = false;
1640  if (map->IsDynguidForced())
1641  dynguid = true;
1642  if (!dynguid)
1643  {

1645  dynguid = true;
1646  }
1647 
1648  if (dynguid || newGuid == 0)
1649  newGuid = map->GenerateLocalLowGuid(cinfo->GetHighGuid());
1650 
1651  Position dbPos(data->posX, data->posY, data->posZ, data->orientation);
1652  if (transport)

1654

1656

1658  return false;
1659

1663

1665  SetStringId(groupEntry->StringId, true);

1667 
1668  SetRespawnCoord(pos);
1669  m_respawnradius = data->spawndist;
1670 
1671  m_respawnDelay = data->GetRandomRespawnTime();
1672  if (!IsUsingNewSpawningSystem())
1673  m_corpseDelay = std::min(m_respawnDelay * 9 / 10, m_corpseDelay); // set corpse delay to 90% of the respawn delay
1674  m_deathState = ALIVE;
1675 
1676  m_respawnTime = map->GetPersistentState()->GetCreatureRespawnTime(dbGuid);
1677 
1678  if (m_respawnTime > time(nullptr)) // not ready to respawn
1679  {
1680  m_deathState = DEAD;
1681  SetHealth(0);
1682  if (CanFly())
1683  {
1684  float tz = GetTerrain()->GetHeightStatic(data->posX, data->posY, data->posZ, false);
1685  if (data->posZ - tz > 0.1)
1686  Relocate(data->posX, data->posY, tz);
1687  }
1688  }
1689  else if (m_respawnTime) // respawn time set but expired
1690  {
1691  m_respawnTime = 0;
1692 
1693  GetMap()->GetPersistentState()->SaveCreatureRespawnTime(dbGuid, 0);
1694  }
1695 
1696  if (sCreatureLinkingMgr.IsSpawnedByLinkedMob(this))
1697  {
1698  m_isSpawningLinked = true;
1699  if (m_deathState == ALIVE && !GetMap()->GetCreatureLinkingHolder()->CanSpawn(this))
1700  {
1701  m_deathState = DEAD;
1702  SetHealth(0);
1703

1705  if (CanFly())
1706  {

1708  if (data->posZ - tz > 0.1)
1709  Relocate(data->posX, data->posY, tz);
1710  }
1711  }
1712  }
1713 
1714  if (transport)
1715  {
1716  m_movementInfo.SetTransportPos(Position(data->posX, data->posY, data->posZ, data->orientation));
1717  transport->AddPassenger(this);
1718  }
1719 
1720  map->Add(this);
1721 
1722  AIM_Initialize();
1723 
1724  if (data && data->spawnTemplate->relayId)
1725  GetMap()->ScriptsStart(SCRIPT_TYPE_RELAY, data->spawnTemplate->relayId, this, nullptr);
1726 
1727  // Creature Linking, Initial load is handled like respawn
1728  if (m_isCreatureLinkingTrigger && IsAlive())
1729  GetMap()->GetCreatureLinkingHolder()->DoCreatureLinkingEvent(LINKING_EVENT_RESPAWN, this);
1730 
1731  if (GetCreatureGroup())
1732  {
1733  auto fData = m_creatureGroup->GetFormationData();
1734  if (fData)
1735  fData->SetFormationSlot(this);
1736  GetCreatureGroup()->TriggerLinkingEvent(CREATURE_GROUP_EVENT_RESPAWN, this);
1737  }
1738 
1739  // check if it is rabbit day
1740  if (IsAlive() && sWorld.getConfig(CONFIG_UINT32_RABBIT_DAY))
1741  {
1742  time_t rabbit_day = time_t(sWorld.getConfig(CONFIG_UINT32_RABBIT_DAY));
1743  tm rabbit_day_tm = *localtime(&rabbit_day);
1744  tm now_tm = *localtime(&sWorld.GetGameTime());
1745 
1746  if (now_tm.tm_mon == rabbit_day_tm.tm_mon && now_tm.tm_mday == rabbit_day_tm.tm_mday)
1747  CastSpell(this, 10710 + urand(0, 2), TRIGGERED_OLD_TRIGGERED);
1748  }
1749 
1750  return true;
1751 }

1846 void Creature::SetDeathState(DeathState s)
1847 {

1864

1993 SpellEntry const* Creature::ReachWithSpellAttack(Unit* pVictim)
1994 {
1995  if (!pVictim)
1996  return nullptr;
1997 
1998  for (auto& data : m_spellList.Spells)
1999  {
2000  uint32 spellId = data.second.SpellId;

2012  {
2013  if ((j == SPELL_EFFECT_SCHOOL_DAMAGE) ||
2014  (j == SPELL_EFFECT_INSTAKILL) ||

2029  float minrange = GetSpellMinRange(srange);
2030 
2031  float dist = GetDistance(pVictim, true, spellInfo->rangeIndex == SPELL_RANGE_IDX_COMBAT ? DIST_CALC_COMBAT_REACH_WITH_MELEE : DIST_CALC_COMBAT_REACH);

2034  // continue;
2035  if (dist > range || dist < minrange)
2036  continue;
2037  if (spellInfo->PreventionType == SPELL_PREVENTION_TYPE_SILENCE && HasFlag(UNIT_FIELD_FLAGS, UNIT_FLAG_SILENCED))
2038  continue;
2039  if (spellInfo->PreventionType == SPELL_PREVENTION_TYPE_PACIFY && HasFlag(UNIT_FIELD_FLAGS, UNIT_FLAG_PACIFIED))

2042  }

2508 uint32 Creature::GetVendorItemCurrentCount(VendorItem const* vItem)
2509 {
2510  if (!vItem->maxcount)
2511  return vItem->maxcount;
2512 
2513  VendorItemCounts::iterator itr = m_vendorItemCounts.begin();
2514  for (; itr != m_vendorItemCounts.end(); ++itr)
2515  if (itr->itemId == vItem->item)
2516  break;
2517 
2518  if (itr == m_vendorItemCounts.end())
2519  return vItem->maxcount;
2520 
2521  VendorItemCount* vCount = &*itr;
2522 
2523  time_t ptime = time(nullptr);
2524 
2525  if (vCount->lastIncrementTime + vItem->incrtime <= ptime)
2526  {
2527  ItemPrototype const* pProto = ObjectMgr::GetItemPrototype(vItem->item);
2528 
2529  uint32 diff = uint32((ptime - vCount->lastIncrementTime) / vItem->incrtime);
2530  if ((vCount->count + diff * pProto->BuyCount) >= vItem->maxcount)
2531  {
2532  m_vendorItemCounts.erase(itr);
2533  return vItem->maxcount;
2534  }
2535 
2536  vCount->count += diff * pProto->BuyCount;
2537  vCount->lastIncrementTime = ptime;
2538  }
2539 
2540  return vCount->count;
2541 }
2542 
2543 uint32 Creature::UpdateVendorItemCurrentCount(VendorItem const* vItem, uint32 used_count)
2544 {
2545  if (!vItem->maxcount)
2546  return 0;
2547 
2548  VendorItemCounts::iterator itr = m_vendorItemCounts.begin();
2549  for (; itr != m_vendorItemCounts.end(); ++itr)
2550  if (itr->itemId == vItem->item)
2551  break;
2552 
2553  if (itr == m_vendorItemCounts.end())
2554  {
2555  uint32 new_count = vItem->maxcount > used_count ? vItem->maxcount - used_count : 0;
2556  m_vendorItemCounts.push_back(VendorItemCount(vItem->item, new_count));
2557  return new_count;
2558  }
2559 
2560  VendorItemCount* vCount = &*itr;
2561 
2562  time_t ptime = time(nullptr);
2563 
2564  if (vCount->lastIncrementTime + vItem->incrtime <= ptime)
2565  {
2566  ItemPrototype const* pProto = ObjectMgr::GetItemPrototype(vItem->item);
2567 
2568  uint32 diff = uint32((ptime - vCount->lastIncrementTime) / vItem->incrtime);
2569  if ((vCount->count + diff * pProto->BuyCount) < vItem->maxcount)
2570  vCount->count += diff * pProto->BuyCount;
2571  else
2572  vCount->count = vItem->maxcount;
2573  }
2574 
2575  vCount->count = vCount->count > used_count ? vCount->count - used_count : 0;
2576  vCount->lastIncrementTime = ptime;
2577  return vCount->count;
2578 }

2616 void Creature::ClearTemporaryFaction()
2617 {
2618  // No restore if creature is charmed/possessed.
2619  // For later we may consider extend to restore to charmer faction where charmer is creature.
2620  // This can also be done by update any pet/charmed of creature at any faction change to charmer.

2626  // Reset UNIT_FLAG_SPAWNING, UNIT_FLAG_IMMUNE_TO_PLAYER, UNIT_FLAG_IMMUNE_TO_NPC, UNIT_FLAG_PACIFIED or UNIT_FLAG_UNINTERACTIBLE flags

2628  SetFlag(UNIT_FIELD_FLAGS, UNIT_FLAG_SPAWNING);

2788 // Set loot status. Also handle remove corpse timer
2789 void Creature::SetLootStatus(CreatureLootStatus status, bool forced)
2790 {
2791  if (!forced && status <= m_lootStatus)
2792  return;
2793 
2794  m_lootStatus = status;
2795  switch (status)
2796  {
2797  case CREATURE_LOOT_STATUS_LOOTED:
2798  if (m_creatureInfo->SkinningLootId)
2799  SetFlag(UNIT_FIELD_FLAGS, UNIT_FLAG_SKINNABLE);
2800  else
2801  {
2802  // there is no loot so we can degrade corpse decay
2803  ReduceCorpseDecayTimer();
2804  RemoveFlag(UNIT_DYNAMIC_FLAGS, UNIT_DYNFLAG_LOOTABLE);
2805  }
2806  break;
2807  case CREATURE_LOOT_STATUS_SKINNED:
2808  m_corpseExpirationTime = TimePoint(); // remove corpse at next update
2809  RemoveFlag(UNIT_FIELD_FLAGS, UNIT_FLAG_SKINNABLE);
2810  RemoveFlag(UNIT_DYNAMIC_FLAGS, UNIT_DYNFLAG_LOOTABLE);
2811  break;
2812  case CREATURE_LOOT_STATUS_SKIN_AVAILABLE:
2813  SetFlag(UNIT_FIELD_FLAGS, UNIT_DYNFLAG_LOOTABLE);
2814  RemoveFlag(UNIT_FIELD_FLAGS, UNIT_FLAG_SKINNABLE);
2815  break;
2816  case CREATURE_LOOT_STATUS_PICKPOCKETED:
2817  StartPickpocketRestockTimer();
2818  break;
2819  default:
2820  break;
2821  }
2822 }

3054 void Creature::AddCooldown(SpellEntry const& spellEntry, ItemPrototype const* /*itemProto*/, bool permanent, uint32 forcedDuration, bool ignoreCat /*= false*/)
3055 {
3056  uint32 recTime = forcedDuration ? forcedDuration : spellEntry.RecoveryTime;
3057  uint32 categoryRecTime = ignoreCat ? 0 : spellEntry.CategoryRecoveryTime;
3058  if (!forcedDuration)
3059  {
3060  uint32 cooldown = 0;
3061  Creature::CooldownResult result = GetSpellCooldown(spellEntry.Id, cooldown);
3062  bool success = result != COOLDOWN_RESULT_NOT_FOUND;
3063  if (!success)
3064  success = sObjectMgr.GetCreatureCooldown(GetCreatureInfo()->Entry, spellEntry.Id, cooldown);
3065  if (success && cooldown) // lets see if this will one day become a problem, if it does, add -1 -1 defaults to creature spell lists
3066  {
3067  if (result == COOLDOWN_RESULT_FOUND)
3068  recTime = cooldown;
3069  else if (result == COOLDOWN_RESULT_CATEGORY_FOUND)
3070  categoryRecTime = cooldown;
3071  }
3072  }
3073  if (recTime || categoryRecTime)
3074  {
3075  if (Player* modOwner = GetSpellModOwner())
3076  {
3077  if (recTime)
3078  modOwner->ApplySpellMod(spellEntry.Id, SPELLMOD_COOLDOWN, recTime);
3079  else if (spellEntry.Category && categoryRecTime)
3080  modOwner->ApplySpellMod(spellEntry.Id, SPELLMOD_COOLDOWN, categoryRecTime);
3081  }
3082 
3083  m_cooldownMap.AddCooldown(GetMap()->GetCurrentClockTime(), spellEntry.Id, recTime, spellEntry.Category, categoryRecTime, 0, permanent);
3084  }
3085  if ((recTime || categoryRecTime))
3086  {
3087  if (Player const* player = dynamic_cast<Player const*>(GetMaster()))
3088  {
3089  if (spellEntry.HasAttribute(SPELL_ATTR_COOLDOWN_ON_EVENT) && !permanent)
3090  {
3091  WorldPacket data(SMSG_COOLDOWN_EVENT, (4 + 8));
3092  data << uint32(spellEntry.Id);
3093  data << GetObjectGuid();
3094  player->GetSession()->SendPacket(data);
3095  }
3096  else
3097  {
3098  // send to client
3099  WorldPacket data(SMSG_SPELL_COOLDOWN, 8 + 1 + 4);
3100  data << GetObjectGuid();
3101  data << uint8(1);
3102  data << uint32(spellEntry.Id);
3103  data << uint32(recTime);
3104  player->GetSession()->SendPacket(data);
3105  }
3106  }
3107  }
3108 }
